    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available for acquisition is a mechanically robust 2004 BMW M3 (E46). This example is powered by the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six engine, featuring individual throttle bodies and a recently serviced double-VANOS system for optimal cam phasing. The drivetrain is anchored by a tactile 6-speed manual gearbox and an M-variable limited-slip differential. To ensure structural longevity, the rear subframe has been professionally reinforced, addressing a known chassis fatigue point. The suspension maintains its factory-spec poise with refreshed bushings, offering the precise turn-in and communicative feedback the E46 is renowned for. While the bodywork displays minor patina reflective of a well-enjoyed enthusiast vehicle, the powertrain and underpinnings are dialed in for spirited performance. This is a turn-key machine for the purist who prioritizes mechanical excellence and driving dynamics.",
      "price": 34500.0,
      "reputation": 0.8,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 13
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_3_listing_3",
